      "repair_reason": "- [P1] Human-only until the external contributor supplies real behavior proof; there is no narrow code defect for ClawSweeper to repair automatically.; Cleared: The diff only clears an existing local timer handle and does not change command sources, dependencies, CI, permissions, secrets, package resolution, or user-controlled input handling. (sha=c47caad7a80fdcd3362a6ab07d3176aa540b8e22)",
      "review_summary": "The branch modifies `src/infra/tailscale.ts` so the Tailscale binary probe stores the manual timeout handle and clears it in a `finally` block.\n\nPR surface: Source +5. Total +5 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. by source inspection: current main schedules a manual timeout inside `checkBinary` and cannot clear it when `runExec` wins the race. I did not run a live Tailscale discovery command in this read-only review.",
